## Summary

The teams Personal session agent has been writing bug todo files directly
into the project repo via `file_write`, bypassing the `bl bug` CLI workflow.
~/.clawq/daemon.log (2026-05-21 17:20:46 + 17:21:15) shows two file_writes:

```
file_write path=/home/xertrov/src/clawq/.backlog/bugs/B605-claude-model-claude-code-creds-needs-flag.todo
file_write path=/home/xertrov/src/clawq/.backlog/bugs/B605-claude-model-claude-code-creds-needs-flag.todo
```

(Two writes to the same file 29s apart — the second overwrote the first.)

Concerns:

1. **Workspace escape.** The agent's CWD/effective workspace should not
   include `/home/xertrov/src/clawq/.backlog/`. The teams agent template
   should restrict write paths so backlog ingestion is done through `bl`,
   which validates ID allocation, format, and indexing.

2. **ID collision risk.** B605 already exists in the backlog. A direct
   file_write that picks an arbitrary ID risks overwriting (or shadowing)
   a real entry. `bl bug` allocates the next free B-id atomically.

3. **Format drift.** The content the agent wrote did not match `bl`'s
   schema (mixing YAML and markdown sections in a way that the index/sync
   commands may misparse).

4. **Hallucinated content.** The bug text refers to 'CLaude-ha credentials'
   and an 'Anthropic policy change' — neither of those phrases appears
   anywhere in the repo or in any Anthropic public communication. The
   agent invented a non-existent policy and was about to file a bug
   prescribing config changes for it.

## Suggested fix

1. Restrict the teams agent template (`src/agent_template_builtins.ml`)
   so `file_write` cannot target paths under `/.backlog/`. Force backlog
   creation to go through `shell_exec` with `bl bug --simple ...` (which
   is what the agent successfully did for B616 earlier in the same session).
2. Add a workspace-boundary unit test asserting that `.backlog/` writes
   from teams agents are rejected by the workspace path policy.
3. Periodically run `bl admin --check-orphans` (or equivalent) to detect
   `.todo` files in `.backlog/bugs/` that the index doesn't know about.

## Evidence

- ~/.clawq/daemon.log, 17:20:46 + 17:21:15 — two file_write entries
- Session: teams:personal:a:1JPVFng...
- File still on disk if not cleaned: /home/xertrov/src/clawq/.backlog/bugs/B605-claude-model-claude-code-creds-needs-flag.todo